class PhysicsSimulation:
    def __init__(self, width=400, height=400):
        self.root = tk.Tk()
        self.root.title('Physics Acceleration Simulation')
        self.width = width
        self.height = height
        self.canvas = tk.Canvas(self.root, width=self.width, height=self.height, bg='white')
        self.canvas.pack()

        # Ball properties
        self.ball_radius = 15
        self.ball_x = self.width // 2
        self.ball_y = self.ball_radius + 1  # start near top
        self.ball = self.canvas.create_oval(self.ball_x - self.ball_radius, 
                                             self.ball_y - self.ball_radius, 
                                             self.ball_x + self.ball_radius, 
                                             self.ball_y + self.ball_radius, 
                                             fill='blue')

        # Physics parameters
        self.vy = 0.0          # vertical velocity
        self.gravity = 0.5     # gravitational acceleration
        self.jump_velocity = -12  # velocity imparted by jump
        self.bounce_damping = 0.7  # bounce energy loss
        
        # Threshold to allow jump even when mid-air if bounce is too low
        self.jump_threshold = self.height - 50

        # Flag to check if space is pressed, to add extra upward acceleration (if needed)
        self.space_pressed = False

        # Bind the spacebar press
        self.root.bind('<KeyPress-space>', self.on_space_press)

        # Start simulation
        self.update()
        self.root.mainloop()
        
    def on_space_press(self, event):
        # When space is pressed, trigger jump if near the floor or if ball hasn't bounced high
        # Check if ball is on the floor or near it
        floor = self.height - 5
        if self.ball_y + self.ball_radius >= floor - 1 or self.ball_y >= self.jump_threshold:
            # trigger jump
            self.vy = self.jump_velocity
        else:
            # Optionally, if midair and bounce is too low, allow jump boost
            if self.vy > 0 and self.ball_y >= self.jump_threshold - 20:
                self.vy = self.jump_velocity

    def update(self):
        # Apply gravity
        self.vy += self.gravity
        self.ball_y += self.vy
        floor = self.height - 5  # Define a floor a bit above the bottom
        
        # Bounce when hitting the floor
        if self.ball_y + self.ball_radius >= floor:
            self.ball_y = floor - self.ball_radius
            # Reverse velocity with damping
            self.vy = -self.vy * self.bounce_damping
            # If bounce is very small, set velocity to 0
            if abs(self.vy) < 1.5:
                self.vy = 0
        
        # Update the ball's position on canvas
        self.canvas.coords(self.ball, 
                           self.ball_x - self.ball_radius, 
                           self.ball_y - self.ball_radius, 
                           self.ball_x + self.ball_radius, 
                           self.ball_y + self.ball_radius)
        
        # Schedule the next frame
        self.root.after(16, self.update)  # ~60 FPS

if __name__ == '__main__':
    PhysicsSimulation()

import time

class PhysicsSimulation:
    def __init__(self, width=400, height=400):
        self.root = tk.Tk()
        self.root.title('Physics Acceleration Simulation')
        self.width = width
        self.height = height
        self.canvas = tk.Canvas(self.root, width=self.width, height=self.height, bg='white')
        self.canvas.pack()

        # Ball properties
        self.ball_radius = 15
        self.ball_x = self.width // 2
        self.ball_y = self.ball_radius + 1  # start near top
        self.ball = self.canvas.create_oval(self.ball_x - self.ball_radius,
                                             self.ball_y - self.ball_radius,
                                             self.ball_x + self.ball_radius,
                                             self.ball_y + self.ball_radius,
                                             fill='blue')

        # Physics parameters
        self.vy = 0.0               # vertical velocity
        self.normal_gravity = 0.5   # normal gravitational acceleration
        self.space_gravity = self.normal_gravity * 1000  # gravity when space is pressed
        self.jump_velocity = -20    # more aggressive jump velocity
        self.bounce_damping = 0.9   # reduced energy loss for higher bounce
        
        # Threshold: reduce the height requirement for bounce/jump
        self.jump_threshold = self.height - 10

        # Create text items on canvas to show the speed and frequency
        self.speed_text = self.canvas.create_text(10, 10, anchor='nw', text='Speed: 0.00', font=('Arial', 12))
        self.freq_text = self.canvas.create_text(self.width - 10, 10, anchor='ne', text='Freq: 0.00', font=('Arial', 12))
        
        # Variables for frame frequency measuring
        self.last_time = time.time()
        
        # Flag to track if space is currently pressed
        self.space_active = False

        # Bind the spacebar press and release events
        self.root.bind('<KeyPress-space>', self.on_space_press)
        self.root.bind('<KeyRelease-space>', self.on_space_release)

        # Start simulation
        self.update()
        self.root.mainloop()

    def on_space_press(self, event):
        # Mark space as active
        self.space_active = True
        floor = self.height - 5
        # If the ball is nearly on the floor, perform a jump
        if self.ball_y + self.ball_radius >= floor - 1 or self.ball_y >= self.jump_threshold:
            self.vy = self.jump_velocity

    def on_space_release(self, event):
        # Mark space as inactive
        self.space_active = False

    def update(self):
        # Calculate frame frequency
        current_time = time.time()
        dt = current_time - self.last_time
        self.last_time = current_time
        frequency = 1 / dt if dt > 0 else 0

        # Determine which gravity to use
        current_gravity = self.space_gravity if self.space_active else self.normal_gravity
        
        # Apply gravity
        self.vy += current_gravity
        self.ball_y += self.vy
        floor = self.height - 5
        
        # Bounce when hitting the floor
        if self.ball_y + self.ball_radius >= floor:
            self.ball_y = floor - self.ball_radius
            # Reverse velocity with damping
            self.vy = -self.vy * self.bounce_damping
            # If bounce is very small, set velocity to 0
            if abs(self.vy) < 1.5:
